COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_TYP_CD IS 'A unique code value to identify the specific premium discount program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_LVL_LO_PCT IS 'The smallest amount of premium which a policy can have to qualify for this program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_LVL_HI_PCT IS 'The largest amount of premium which a policy can have to qualify for this program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_END_DT IS 'The date that the premium discount program is no longer in effect.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_RT IS 'The actual rate associated with this premium discount program.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.RT_ELEM_PREM_DSCNT_VOID_IND IS 'An indicator identifying whether the record has been logically deleted or not.';
comment on column RATING_ELEMENT_PREM_DSCNT.CNCURNCY_ID is 'This column needs to be used only for optimistic concurrency support ONLY.';


